    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for the `next/geo` module:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### Files to create/modify (5 total)\n\n| Action | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| **Modify** | `packages/next/package.json` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `geo.ts` (core implementation)\nMirrors `user-agent.ts` pattern exactly. Key design decisions:\n- `Geo` interface with 7 optional string fields\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries: US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — reads Vercel headers (`x-vercel-ip-*`), falls back to `cf-ipcountry` for Cloudflare, resolves `country` name from map\n- `geo(req: { headers: Headers }): Geo` — thin wrapper (same pattern as `userAgent` wrapping `userAgentFromString`)\n- `isInRegion(geo: Geo, regions: string[]): boolean` — case-insensitive countryCode membership\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2): number` — Haversine formula in km\n- Uses `?? undefined` (not `|| undefined`) to safely convert `null` header results → TypeScript strict-safe\n\n### Step 2 — `geo.js` (public CJS entry)\nMirrors `server.js` pattern: aggregated object assignment + repeated `exports.X = geoExports.X` for named import support. Uses `require('next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo')` paths.\n\n### Step 3 — `geo.d.ts` (type declarations)\nMirrors `server.d.ts`: named `export type { Geo }` and `export { geo, geoFromHeaders, isInRegion, geoDistance }` from `'next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo'`.\n\n### Step 4 — `package.json` files array\nInsert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (line 43) — the alphabetically correct slot (f → **g** → h).\n\n### Step 5 — `geo.test.ts`\n10 test cases using `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` (no external framework):\n- Vercel headers (all 7 fields + country name resolution)\n- Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` fallback\n- Missing headers → all `undefined`, no crash\n- `x-vercel-ip-country` priority over `cf-ipcountry`\n- `isInRegion`: match, no-match, case-insensitive, undefined countryCode\n- `geoDistance`: NYC→London ≈5570 km ±50 km, identical points = 0\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types                          # Type check\npnpm --filter=next build                          # Compile src → dist\nnode --test packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts  # Unit tests\nnode -e \"console.log(Object.keys(require('./packages/next/geo.js')))\" # Smoke test\n```",
